members.name: periods
members.doc:
Times that this object is available. Each period represents a range of hours when the object is
available during the week. Limited to 100 time periods.

members.name: locationId
members.doc: The location id that the catalog refers to

members.name: revision
members.doc: Catalog revision, represents the number of changes to the catalog.

members.name: availableChoices
members.doc: List of available choices for the option.

members.name: price
members.doc: Option price. When an option price is included in the item price, price = null.

members.name: availableChoices
members.doc: List of available choices for the option.

members.name: maxChoices
members.doc: Max number of options allowed to be chosen for this item. default available_choices size, must be equal or bigger than min choices

members.name: minChoices
members.doc: Number of options required to be chosen for this item. default 0, max value is available_choices size

members.name: includeCondition
members.doc: Default: false. Returns condition data of item

members.name: allowSpecialRequest
members.doc: Allow the user to enter special request for this item, Default value is true

members.name: archived
members.doc: Whether this item is archived. Archived item can't be updated.

members.name: externalId
members.doc: External id of the item - this field is managed and send by client.

members.name: soldOut
members.doc: Whether this item is sold out.

members.name: visibilityCriteria
members.doc:
Any visibility criteria required in order for this item to be displayed in the restaurant’s menu.
In case of multiple visibility criteria, all must be true for the item to be displayed.

description:
A span of time that the object is available,
starting on the specified open day/time and closing on the specified close day/time.
Closing time must occur after the opening time, for example later in the same day, or on a subsequent day.

members.name: closeDay
members.doc: Day of the week this period ends on.

members.name: closeTime
members.doc:
Time in 24hr ISO 8601 extended format (hh:mm). Valid values are 00:00-24:00, where 24:00 represents
midnight at the end of the specified day field.

members.name: openDay
members.doc: Day of the week this period starts on.

members.name: openTime
members.doc:
Time in 24hr ISO 8601 extended format (hh:mm). Valid values are 00:00-24:00, where 24:00 represents
midnight at the end of the specified day field.
